<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kuuin</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-02 01:06:13</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>It really amazes me how much speculative crap people post when they have no clue what is going on. I have personally killed Grazhak once, and forced him to spawn again 2 days later. Unfortunately the 2nd time I had given up for the night only to have a friend tell me Grazhak showed no more than 15 mins later. He spawns near the Feerot zone and as far as I can tell his placeholders are orcs, lizardmen, bears, skels, fire beetles and such. I have a feeling that its mainly the wandering orcs, either priests or warriors, but everything is of such low level why not kill them all? Concentrate on killing all wandering spawns in the area where the 2 undead camps are to the left coming out of the Feerot zone. Don't bother clearing the orc camp it has nothing to do with his spawn at all. Do however clear all wanderes in the area I mentioned and also check the xroads by the Feerot zone and kill anything that cruises in there, usually a bear, lizard scout or skeletons. When I found Grazhak the first time he was coming from the xroads towards the open area where you will be concentrating on clearing spawns.<BR>
<BR>
I have screenshots to prove what I say and I might camp him again soon as I am more confident in my method after causing his 2nd spawn 2 days later. Also if you're clearing lizardmen, basilisks and drakes you have a chance to get Petrifin, Mortificator and Shardwing to spawn. By the way he had the girth when I killed him which promptly traded for a Mortificator staff :)<BR>
<BR>
Kuuin<BR>
Level 50 Druid<BR>
The Rathe</font></td></tr></table>
